HEADWORD: cabbageworm
<hw>cab"bage*worm`</hw></mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld>, <def>the larva of several species
of moths and butterflies, which attacks cabbages. The most common is the
toxic green larva of a white butterfly, the <er>cabbage butterfly</er>,
(<spn>Pieris rap⟦ae⟧</spn>). The cabbage cutworms, which eat off the
stalks of young plants during the night, are the larv⟦ae⟧ of several
species of moths, of the genus <gen>Agrotis</gen>. See <er>Cutworm</er>.
larva of a cabbage butterfly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

